				<td><font face="arial,verdana,helvetica" size="2" color="#CCCCCC"><h2 class="header2"><img src="../images/headers/hdr_prai.gif" width="99" height="62" alt="" 
border="0"><br />The four star Prescott Hotel is considered one of San Francisco's best hotels</h2>

				
				<p>We are proud of the Mobil four star and AAA four diamond awards our small luxury hotel has received as well as recognition from guests and media alike as one of the best hotels in San Francisco. Here are some of the awards and reviews we've received:</p>

                <li>AAA Four Diamond Award, 2006</li>				
				<li><a href="http://www.ciwmb.ca.gov/EPP/GreenLodging" target="_blank">California EPA Green Lodging Program, Participation level</a></li>
				<li><img src="../images/bn_t-l-500.gif" width="135" height="181" alt="" border="0" align="right">AAA Four Diamond Award, July 2004<br /><br /></li>
				<li><em>Travel &amp; Leisure Magazine</em>, <em>T&amp;L Value Guide</em> <strong style="color:#ffcc00">Rated #3 Best Value Hotel</strong>, 2004<br /><br /></li>
				<li><em>Conde Nast Traveler Magazine</em> (January 2003, January 2004) <em style="color:#ffcc00">Gold List: The World's Best Places to Stay </em> The Prescott Hotel - It 	"brings the city's best indoors," including "terrific" Pan-Asian food at Wolfgang Puck's Postrio."Near everything downtown," this "trendy" boutique hotel "works well for business types." Staff seem "very happy to help with everything."<br /><br /></li>
				<li><em>Conde Nast Traveler Magazine</em> (November 2001), <em>2001 Readers' Choice Awards: <strong style="color:#ffcc00">Top 50 North American Hotels</strong>:</em> The Prescott Hotel, San Francisco<br /><br /></li>
				<li>"Impeccably designed hotel with a 'European' ambiance…quietly elegant…perfect [service]: helpful attention with smart appearance and a smile. Staff seem genuinely interested in you."	- <em>Conde Nast Traveler</em><br /><br /></li>

				
				Sunday Business section, <em>London Pink Pages</em>, excerpted from "You can still leave your heart in San Francisco", by Jeff Mills, Travel Editor:<br /><br />
				
				<p>"One of the best San Francisco hotels is the Prescott Hotel at 545 Post Street, between Taylor and Mason Streets and no more than five minutes' walk from Union Square. A small, stylish boutique hotel owned by Kimpton Hotels, one of a dozen such properties in San Francisco developed by the company since its founder, Bill Kimpton, abandoned Wall Street for the hotel and restaurant business in 1981.</p>
				  
				<p>The Prescott follows the company's usual formula of taking an old building and converting it into a small, elegant town-house-style hotel - perfect if you prefer to stay in a property where the staff not only recognize your face but remember your name and how you like your morning coffee. Stay here and you will be well advised to pay a little extra and book a room on one of the executive floors which come complete with complimentary continental breakfast and free early-evening drinks in the fourth-floor club lounge.</p>
				
				<p>Another advantage of staying here, in a city where top restaurants are booked up weeks in advance, is that one of the best, Postrio, is not only rights next door and even has a door direct from the hotel's lobby, but guests at the Prescott receive preferential treatment when it comes to allocating tables for the evening. Just one of the services provided by the hotel's concierges designed to make life easier for business travellers."</p>

<li>Note: for Postrio Reservations call the hotel directly</li>

</font></td>
